37\u00b0C<\/span><span>, then <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">skip to Step 5. Number of reuses will depend on sample type and concentration used. <\/span><span style = \"font-style:italic;\"><\/span><\/div><br\/><\/div>"}},{"id":1054725,"guid":"1391B620A9C511EB9E84A31B888D0C37","order_id":2,"type_id":4,"title":"duration","source":{"duration":1800,"title":""}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":120,"critical":[{"id":1,"title":"Incubation","icon":"IncubationIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":1800},{"id":1170997,"guid":"78958820A9C111EBA6716B4AA988B374","previous_id":1170996,"previous_guid":"788FBBC0A9C111EBA6716B4AA988B374","modified_on":0,"protocol_id":0,"components":[{"id":1054723,"guid":"B1C04B1FAB2A46CEA142F38B9DE36A5D","order_id":1,"type_id":6,"title":"Section","source":{"title":"Day 1 "}},{"id":1054724,"guid":"F8D9387EBF214C03B8C593BB4FD50A48","order_id":1,"type_id":1,"title":"description","source":{"description":"<div class = \"text-blocks\"><div class = \"text-block\"><span>Prepare probe solution by adding 0.8pmol (0.8\u00b5l of probe from 1uM stock solution) of each probe mixture to 200\u00b5L of probe hybridization buffer at <\/span><span style = \"font-weight:bold;\">37\u00b0C<\/span><span>. <\/span><\/div><br\/><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><span style = \"font-style:italic;\">Troubleshooting tip: If signals are weak, try increasing probe concentration up to 2-3x. We have found this increased probe concentration to be useful when dealing with shorter than recommended starting sequences (fewer probe sets).<\/span><\/div><\/div><div class = \"text-block\"><div class = \"justify\" style = \"text-align:left\"><\/div><\/div><\/div>"}}],"cases":[],"data":null,"html":null,"section":null,"section_color":"#A492FF","section_duration":120,"critical":[{"id":1,"title":"Incubation","icon":"IncubationIcon"}],"critical_id":null,"duration":0},{"id